==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mawmet
<hw>Maw"met</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Contr. fr.
<ets>Mahomet</ets>.]</ety> <def>A puppet; a doll; originally, an idol,
because in the Middle Ages it was generally but falsely believed that
the Muslims worshiped images representing
<persfn>Mohammed</persfn>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyclif.
Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

